We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the General Services Officer (GSO), BAC Secretariat and all the Department Heads to:
Formulate the Municipality’s APP in accordance with Section 7 of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184;
Ensure that all the necessary information required in the APP and its amendments are reflected therein for its continuous relevance and usefulness as a planning and control tool;
Submit the duly approved copy of APP to the GPPB in accordance with Section 1(a) of Executive Order No. 662, series of 2007, as amended; and
Include in the APP, provisions for foreseeable emergencies based on historical records as well as the manner of procurement thereof.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Bids and Awards Committee to strictly comply with the provision of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of Infrastructure Projects, particularly, Annex H Consolidated Guidelines for the Alternative Methods of Procurement;

Municipal Engineer to strictly monitor implementation of contract and ensure compliance with Annexes E of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 and with the full disclosure policy by taking photographs of signboard as an integral part of supporting documents for claim of payment;

Municipal Accountant to properly recognize cost to appropriate accounts and submit the complete and duly authenticated supporting documents prescribed under Section 9.2.5 of COA Circular No. 2012-001; and

BAC/GSO to observe the timely submission of advance copies of contracts within five (5) working days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Bids and Awards Committee to strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of goods;

BAC to demand from the Supplier the posting of performance security and warranty security in order to fully protect the interest of the Municipality in case of manufacturing defects and failures;

Municipal Accountant to review the regularity and completeness of supporting documents prescribed under Section 9.1 of COA Circular No. 2012 – 001 before processing claims for payment; and

BAC/GSO to observe the timely submission of advance copies of contracts within five (5) working days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001.

We reiterated our recommendation that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Accountant to:

exert extra effort to account the unreconciled items of two (2) PNB accounts appearing in the BRS of the LBP accounts to faithfully present the correct balances of the accounts;

prepare the necessary adjusting entries to record and correct the unrecorded amounts and erroneous entries made in the Cash in Bank account, respectively;

revert to proper Cash in Bank and payable accounts all Stale Checks; and

prepare and submit the BRS together with the bank statements and paid checks for all the Municipality’s bank accounts within the reglementary period.

On the procurement, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the BAC to:

furnish the Audit Team with a copy of the Contract of Agreement and its attachments within five (5) working days from the execution thereof as required under Section 3.1.1 of COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 23, 2009;

observe strictly the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 to ensure adherence to the principles of transparency, competitiveness and public monitoring; 

strengthen internal control over the evaluation of the bids and post-qualification of bidders to ensure timeliness, completeness and veracity of the post-qualified documents as reported in the Bid and Post- Qualification Evaluation Reports;

submit the lacking documents cited above to the Audit Team to comply with the requirements of the 2016 Revised IRR of R.A. 9184 and address the deficiencies enumerated; and 

prepare the required reports/documents with extra care to avoid errors which could mislead readers and users of the reports.

On the payments made, we recommended that the Municipal Accountant as the internal auditor, see to it that supporting documents attached to the vouchers are accurate and complete before processing the claims.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:

Municipal Disaster Risk and Reduction Officer (MDRRMO) to prepare the LDRRMFIP in accordance with the format prescribed in Annex A of COA Circular No. 2012-002. It should also include the list of projects and activities charged to the unexpended LDRRMF of previous years;

Municipal Accountant to effect corrections to the errors and over transfer noted in CY 2017 as well as the over-transfer of fund in CY 2018 to properly present the correct balances of affected  accounts;

Municipal Accountant to strictly adhere with the guidelines set forth by COA Circular No. 2012-002 for proper accounting of the utilization and transfer of LDRRM Fund as well as proper recording of various transactions in the Special Trust Fund and Section 4(6) of PD No. 1445 and COA Circular No. 2012-001 for proper documentation of transactions. She should also be guided by COA Circular No. 2015-009 dated December 1, 2015 in the proper recording of transaction in accordance with Philippine Public Sector Accounting Standards (PPSAS); and

Bids and Awards Committee to strictly adhere to the requirements of COA Circular No. 2009-001 and the 2016 Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 for the submission of contracts/purchase order and for procurement of various goods and services of the municipality, respectively.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

require the strict and uniform implementation of the provisions of COA Circular No. 97-002 on the grant, utilization and liquidation of cash advances to all officials and employees of the municipality;

require all accountable officers and employees to settle/liquidate all their outstanding cash advances by sending confirmation, notification or demand letters. For unliquidated cash advances which are non-moving for more three (3) years, exhaust all remedies to collect or demand to liquidate the unliquidated cash advances, otherwise apply for write off in accordance with the guidelines and procedures prescribed by COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 29, 2016;

secure written approval from the Governor for any official travel outside the province in accordance with Section 96 of R.A. No. 7160;

instruct the Municipal Accountant, as the internal auditor, to see to it that supporting documents attached to the vouchers and liquidation reports are accurate and complete before processing the claims and observe the existing rules and regulations and rates of expenses and allowances for official local and foreign travel of government personnel; and

instruct the Municipal Accountant to properly classify each cash advance transaction in accordance with COA Circular No. 2015-009 and reclassify the balance of Advances to Officers and Employees pertaining to the cash advances of accountable officers who were already not in the service, retired or dead amounting to P88,095.24.

We recommended the following:

The GAD Focal Person submit the endorsed Annual GPB and the GAD AR within the time prescribed under Item V of COA Circular No. 2014-001. Submit also the documents attached to the GPB as mentioned above; 

The Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator (MPDC) spearhead the setting up and maintenance of the GAD database to serve as basis for gender-responsive planning, programming and policy formulation;

The Bids and Awards Committee Members be guided by COA Circular No. 2009-001 in the submission of contract/purchase order and the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 in the procurement of goods and services; and

The Municipal Accountant, as the internal auditor, see to it that supporting documents attached to the vouchers are accurate and complete before processing claims. She should also be guided by COA Circular No. 2015-009 for proper recording of transactions.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
Bids and Awards Committee to strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of Infrastructure Projects, particularly, Annex H Consolidated Guidelines for the Alternative Methods of Procurement;
Municipal Engineer to strictly monitor implementation of contract and ensure compliance with Annexes E of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 and with the full disclosure policy by taking photographs of signboard as an integral part of supporting documents for claim of payment;
Municipal Accountant to properly recognize cost to appropriate accounts and submit the complete and duly authenticated supporting documents prescribed under Section 9.2.5 of COA Circular No. 2012-001; and
BAC/GSO to observe the timely submission of advance copies of contracts within five (5) working days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
Bids and Awards Committee to strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of goods;
BAC to demand from the Supplier the posting of performance security and warranty security in order to fully protect the interest of the Municipality in case of manufacturing defects and failures;
Municipal Accountant to review the regularity and completeness of supporting documents prescribed under Section 9.1 of COA Circular No. 2012 – 001 before processing claims for payment; and
BAC/GSO to observe the timely submission of advance copies of contracts within five (5) working days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

Initiate the recruitment of applicants for vacant positions for three staff who will be responsible for                     (1) administration and training; (2) research and planning; and (3) operations and warning to assist the MDRRMO in the performance of its functions; 

Require the MDRRMO to submit the LDRRM Plan and the LDRRMF Investment Plan as required under Section 4(7) Rule 6 of the IRR of RA No. 10121 and Section 5.1.2 of COA Circular No. 2012-002, respectively;

Require the Municipal Accountant to submit monthly reports on the Sources and Utilization of DRRMF using the prescribed format under Section 5.1.5 of COA Circular No. 2012-002; and

Maximize utilization of the LDRRMF to strengthen the resilience of the constituents to calamities and climate change impacts.

We recommended the following:
The Municipal Government officials and members of the Local Development Council properly plan, identify and prioritize the socio-economic development programs and projects to be implemented during the year to ensure the viability and successful completion of the projects;
The Municipal Engineer coordinate, monitor and evaluate the implementation of the projects to avoid delays and maximize the utilization of the 20% Development Fund in accordance with DILG and DBM Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2011-1 dated April 13, 2011;
Consider realignment of appropriations for projects which were already funded by the national government to other priority development projects of the Municipality.

Based on the foregoing observations, we reiterated our recommendations that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Accountant to:

exert extra effort to account the unreconciled items of two (2) PNB accounts appearing in the Bank Reconciliation Statements of LBP accounts to faithfully present the correct balances of the accounts;

prepare necessary adjusting entries to correct the erroneous entries made in the CIB account;

revert to proper CIB and payable accounts all Stale Checks; and

submit the BRS for all the municipality’s bank accounts within the reglementary period.

We recommended that:

the Municipal Treasurer:

strictly observe the existing rules and regulations governing collections and deposits of government funds;

be more circumspect in the acknowledgement of remittances in terms of accuracy of the data and amount;

instruct all the collectors to ensure completeness of information on the face of official receipts and RCDs such as date and number of the report, the date of verification and acknowledgement and signature of the signatories;

ensure that all the issued and cancelled official receipts are attached to their respective Report of Collections and Deposits; 

observe proper procedures for collections through Agency Accredited Bank;

require the collecting officer who has accountability in the Trust Fund to remit the amount and deposit them intact to avoid the suspicion that such fund was misused and to clear the account Cash Collecting Officer in the General Ledger; and

stop accommodating private checks as prescribed under Section 67 (3) of PD 1445.

the Municipal Accountant ensure the accuracy of the amounts of the recorded transactions and adjust the balance of the accounts affected by the errors in computations, as appropriate. Observe proper procedures in recording of collections through Agency Accredited Bank.

Based on the foregoing observations, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Accountant to:

exert extra effort to account the unreconciled items of two (2) PNB accounts appearing in the Bank Reconciliation Statements of LBP accounts to faithfully present the correct balances of the accounts;

prepare necessary adjusting entries to correct the erroneous entries made in the CIB account;

revert to proper CIB and payable accounts all Stale Checks; and

submit the BRS for all the municipality’s bank accounts within the reglementary period.
